slidetranscripts.Text:
Welcome to the New Faculty workshop.

To view this presentation- click next

You may use the tabs on the left to navigate to specific content

• In your first week, you will be busy with several tasks, related to your teaching and administration of your courses. you’ll pick up your parking pass and ID from the Security office; submit your contract,complete online trainings, confirm the division office location, view your classroom, request orientation to any of the technologies in the classroom, request any additional technologies you need for your classroom and, finally, request access to any Canvas course sites you need for your course.

In order to park in staff or faculty parking at HCC, you will need to get a parking pass. You will also need to get an ID card which will identify you as an HCC employee and also provide you access to your classrooms so you can pick up both your parking pass and your ID at the security office, located in the RCF lobby.

• Please be sure to sign and turn in your contract to the Division Office as soon as possible.

• There are payroll deadlines on the 15th and last day of each month. All pay is via direct deposit.

• If you do not wish to use direct deposit, you will need to sign up with payroll to receive a debit card, which will be credited with your pay amount each payday.

Here is a list of required online trainings that you must complete at HCC. All faculty are responsible for completing these trainings within your first semester. Faculty receive professional development credit for each of the trainings that they complete. The professional development period runs from April 1st to March 30th of each year. To learn how to register for these professional development trainings, please see the register for the professional development slide later in this presentation. For additional information about required trainings and when they need to be completed, click the link that says online required training information.

In order to receive credit for any professional development you take at HCC, you must register for that professional development. You register for professional development training using the myHCC portal. Click the image below to see a brief demonstration of how to register for professional development workshop. Remember it’s always best to register prior to the event. Otherwise, please make sure you register upon completion of the professional development event.

Classroom technology varies between classrooms at HCC. The audio visual services department supports faculty in their use of these technologies in each classroom. Some of those technologies are pictured here. Please contact AV services at extension 4819 if you need an assistance with any of these items in your classroom. Please note that if you require assistance with computers in your classroom, you should be contacting the help desk at extension 4444.
To view images of your classroom, visit the myHCC portal, choose teaching and learning resources, and the view your classroom link. Go ahead and try it now.

Canvas is HCC’s learning management system where instructor’s can create and maintain course material in an online environment.

Instructors use Canvas to post instructional content, discussion prompts, syllabi, student grades and assignments where students have access 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.

For more information using canvas, visit the HCC eLearning site or email them at eLearning@howardcc.edu

Faculty Professional Development comes in many forms at Howard Community College. In all cases, faculty professional development offerings are opened to all faculty unless noted otherwise for specific groups, they are available throughout the year and there are free primary professional development periods in May, August and January. Click on each tab to learn about the different opportunities you have to grow as a professional at Howard Community College.

Workshops are led by faculty and members of the Teaching and Learning Services Division. Most workshops are open to all faculty but some are noted for specific group. Some of the workshops led by the Faculty Development office have included titles such as:

-Classroom Assessement

-Why Don’t They Do the Readings

-Integrating Technology Into Instruction

You should watch for emails alerting you to upcoming workshops or check out the Faculty Development Calendar to see a complete list. You will register for faculty professional development using the MyHCC Portal.

Faculty members can schedule one-on-one consultations in the faculty lab which is pictured here. Instructional designers can help you redesign a lesson, develop a classroom assessment, or just come and observe your classroom and provide confidential feedback. Faculty may receive professional development credit for these consultations, and you can schedule them by emailing IMFacultyLab@howardcc.edu

We understand our adjuncts are joggling many different responsibilities outside of HCC. To support them, we have an adjunct institute held one Saturday each month. The workshops at the institute are very similar to those held during the week, and both full time and adjunct faculty are welcome to attend. Watch for emails alerting you to those upcoming workshops or check out the faculty development to see a complete list. Look for the ones marked adjunct institute.

In the next section you’ll learn how to access your email and other necessary online resources at HCC.

You will receive instructions of how to access HCC’s online password protected resources via an email sent to your personal email account by the office of Human Resources.

Your login is your first initial, first 7 letters of your last name plus the last four digits of your HCC login ID.

· Your email must be checked a minimum of twice a week.

· Only HCC email addresses will be used by Division office staff.

· Mail forwarding available if desired.

If you have any difficulty accessing your HCC email, please contact the help desk by calling them at 443-518-4444. On the next slide, we will show you how to login to your HCC email.
For email, use HCC’s web mail by going to HCC’s website at howardcc.edu. Next, click on tools and resources. Next, click on the email icon, and you will be prompted to enter in your HCC login.

Once you have your login credentials be sure and visit the MyHCC portal to access important information related to your employment at HCC and your courses. You access the MyHCC portal by visiting the HCC homepage at howardcc.edu. Click the Tools and Resources button and click the myHCC icon. You will be prompted to enter your HCC credentials.

Using the HCC Portal-MyHCC you can:

• Check email off campus

• Log into Canvas

• Log into Colleague (on campus only)

• View calendar of events

• Access college forms

• Register for professional development

To register for professional development, you will need the 4 digit number of the course, and know the current Professional development term.

The faculty environment on the HCC portal, provides tools for you to view:

• Class schedule

• Class roster

• Submit grades

• Complete your NA signoff. NA means a student never attended your course.

• You’ll have a number of semester obligations. Some of them occur at the beginning of the semester, others at the end. Point to each of these on the list to learn more about them. On subsequent slides, you’ll get even more detail about each of these requirements.
Under the class roster link, you can view student information. You can also email individual students or your entire class.

An override may be needed for over enrollment, late enrollment or a student dropped for non- payment.

Overrides are forms giving students permission to join a class that is full or has already met twice.

Once the term has begun, registration will only be permitted in classes that have available seats and have not met for the second time.

Please be sure you have classroom space before you give permission for a student to enroll in your class.

It is up to the instructor whether or not to allow a student to join the class.

The Division may grant permission for late entry if you notify the division office by email or phone so that an override form can be completed.

If you decide to permit the student entry into your class, the division office will issue the student an override form.

The student must submit the override form to the office of Records, Registration and Veterans Affairs along with the registration form.

Note that some classes such as labs cannot override full classes.

Check with the division office for specific rules regarding your course.

Using the Faculty link in MyHCC go to NA and Final Grades link to do Grades Submissions:

· All grades including NA grades can be submitted in MyHCC.

· NA grades must be submitted the second week of class. Select the semester and class and add the student to the roster.

· Assign any student that has never come to class a grade of “NA.” This is very important for financial aid purposes, as we do not want students who have never attended class to receive financial aid funds.

· If you have no NA grades then use the “No NA grades signoff” link.

• Comprehensive finals are to be given during exam week, which follows the last week of class.

• The schedule is located on the web and in the Schedule of classes.

• Your exam time is not necessarily the exact same time as your class, so be sure to discuss this with your students at the beginning of the semester.

• To see the current final exam schedule, click on the link.

• Use MyHCC to record final grades.

• Grades are due within 48 hours of your final exam.

• HCC does not use plus or minus grades.

• Any student that has received an “F” will require you to enter the last date of attendance.

• Incompletes can be given only to students who have completed at least 75% of the coursework.

• Your division office will require a copy of your MyHCC grade submission, your gradebook, and your attendance record.

• Please check with the office manager to see if electronic copies are only accepted.

IDEA student evaluations is the assessment tool that HCC uses for student’s ratings of instruction. This is how your students will evaluate you. IDEA is administered the 11th-14th week of the semester.

The IDEA process is completely online for faculty and students. Students complete the survey online and faculty have access to response rates in real-time. At the end of the IDEA process faculty can access their course reports online.

All IDEA correspondence will be sent to your HCC issued email. An IDEA survey announcement will be sent to you the 10th week of the semester with instructions on how to administer the survey and faculty resources pertaining to IDEA.

Check the faculty development calendar for upcoming workshops on IDEA.

We know you want the most out of your teaching experience at HCC. That’s why we’re here to support you. HCC offers a wide range of services: AV support, Help desk, Print shop, Test center, and Security.
Click on the tabs to learn how each of these areas can offer you support.

Parking at HCC can be a challenge, especially during the beginning of each semester, between the hours of 10 and 2.

There are some lots with spaces designated for staff in lot F near the HS building and Lots H and I by the Hickory Ridge building.

You will need an HCC staff parking tag for these designated staff spaces.

The parking garages: East and West garages offer many parking spaces and are often your best bet.

Free shuttle service is available to make parking easier at HCC.

Shuttle service is available Monday – Friday from 8 am - 630 pm

Campus drop off and pick up are at the RCF Building and the HR building

Shuttle service is available at three convenient locations: Hickory Ridge Village Center, Patuxent place (the old Columbia Flier building) and Sterrett place.

Each location is less than 10 minutes each way from campus

The shuttle service from Hickory Ridge village center and Patuxent run every 15 minutes and from Sterrett place every 30 minutes.

You can track the dragon wagon using the Smarttrax app available on apple and android devices.

For every 5 round trip shuttle rides, you will earn a $5 voucher that is redeemable at starbucks, cafe on the quad and simply to go.

For a current shuttle schedule click the Link text ”shuttle information and schedule”: http://www.howardcc.edu/services-support/public-safety/parking-and-transportation/shuttle.html

In the case of inclement weather, be sure and check the HCC webpage for college closing or late opening information. You will see a banner similar to the one that appears here. You should also sign up for HCC’s mobile alert to be notified of any event that impact the college hours. You can also sign up for HCC’s mobile alert system to have late opening or early closing alerts sent directly to your phone or email.

· HCC Mobile Alert System enables you to receive instant notification of important campus information to your cellphone, email, or desktop. You can sign up on our website or click the linked text in this presentation.

· HCC does run several drills each semester, such as a lockdown drill and tornado drill. Your classroom clock, public sirens and loudspeaker announcements will be used to signal the drill, as well as the mobile alert system. The college will alert you via email well in advance of these events.

· Use the mobile alert system to get information on school closings or delays, emergencies and parking issues.

If you have any questions or need additional information about any topic covered in this presentation, please contact your Division office.

Thank you for viewing this presentation!

Welcome to Howard Community College where you can help our students get there from here.
